The paper proposes a method for lossy compression that preserves the distribution of the training data, which involves deep generative models and optimization of the rate-distortion tradeoff. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.MM (Multimedia), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Among these, cs.LG and cs.CV are the most likely categories, as the paper heavily relies on deep generative models and image compression. The other categories are also possible, as the paper involves information theory, multimedia, and AI techniques.
